graph TD
    A[Start: Client lacks high school diploma or GED]

    A --> B{Is the client willing and able to pursue a GED or equivalent?}
    B --> B1[Yes]
    B --> B2[No]

    B1 --> C{Are there barriers to pursuing GED (e.g., time, childcare, transportation, learning difficulties)?}
    C --> C1[Yes]
    C1 --> D[Identify and address barriers]
    D --> E[Connect client with GED programs and support services]
    C --> C2[No]
    C2 --> E[Connect client with GED programs]
    E --> F[Client works toward GED while exploring employment options]

    B2 --> G{Is the client interested in vocational training not requiring a GED?}
    G --> G1[Yes]
    G --> G2[No]

    G1 --> H{Are there trade certifications or licenses the client can pursue without a GED?}
    H --> H1[Yes]
    H1 --> I[Explore programs (e.g., CDL, HVAC certification)]
    I --> J{Are there barriers to participation (e.g., age, legal status, cost, prerequisites)?}
    J --> J1[Yes]
    J1 --> K[Identify and address barriers]
    K --> L[Enroll client in vocational training or certification programs]
    J --> J2[No]
    J2 --> L[Enroll client in vocational training or certification programs]

    H --> H2[No]
    H2 --> M{Can client gain skills through apprenticeships or on-the-job training?}
    M --> M1[Yes]
    M1 --> N[Connect client with apprenticeship programs]
    M --> M2[No]
    M2 --> O[Explore other vocational options or revisit pursuing GED]

    G2 --> P{Is the client interested in immediate employment without a GED?}
    P --> P1[Yes]
    P --> P2[No]

    P1 --> Q{Does the client have work experience or transferable skills?}
    Q --> Q1[Yes]
    Q1 --> R[Match client to jobs leveraging existing skills]
    Q --> Q2[No]
    Q2 --> S[Explore entry-level positions and on-the-job training]

    P2 --> T{Consider alternative options (e.g., supported employment, volunteering, micro-enterprise)}
    T --> U[Connect client with alternative opportunities]

    L & N & R & S & F & U --> V{Assess for other barriers (e.g., literacy, language, disabilities, legal status)}
    V --> V1[Yes]
    V1 --> W[Connect client with support services (e.g., literacy programs, ESL classes, legal aid)]
    V --> V2[No]
    V2 --> X[Proceed]

    W & X --> Y{Does the client require additional support for long-term career advancement?}
    Y --> Y1[Yes]
    Y1 --> Z[Develop plan for continued education and skill development]
    Y --> Y2[No]
    Y2 --> AA[Proceed]

    Z & AA --> AB[Develop comprehensive Action Plan addressing education and employment]
    AB --> AC[End: Tailored Action Plan for client with low education level]
